hat puts their labor forces at the cutting edge of the information society. Using an empirical, comparative approach, this book develops a broad picture of the higher education system in each country in the context of both global and local forces. The authors offer insights into how differing socioeconomic and historic patterns of change and political contexts influence developments in higher education. In asking why each state takes the approach that it does, this work situates a discussion of university expansion and quality in the context of governments' educational policies and reflects on the larger struggles over social goals and the distribution of national resources.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aComparative education. 0aEducation, HigherxBRIC countries. 0aEducation, HigherzBRIC countries. 0aHigher education and statexBRIC countries. 0aHigher education and statezBRIC countries. 4aBRIC countries. 4adevelopment. 4aenrollment growth. 4aglobalization. 4ahigher education expansion. 4ainnovation. 4atuition. 4auniversities. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh1 aDobryakova, Maria, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aFroumin, Isak, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKuhns, Katherine, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLoyalka, Prashant, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTilak, Jandhyala, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWang, Rong, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804786416zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804786416423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cov